title: Limited Categories
text: The only reason I'm giving this app four stars, rather than five, is it would simply seem a no brainer to have a local business services category. When, like most Americans, I'm striving to be both local & environmentally conscientious & have to zoom in excessively, visit other sites online, download yet another app, or research to see what's actually there, it's an extremely time consuming process. I'm supporting local & legitimate business owners that live here. Example: When I need to find someone to mow a lawn, install a security system, etc., I don't want want to speak to someone that lives 800 plus miles away. How can Americans help small local business entrepreneurs grow and be successful, when to do so, it's next to impossible to even obtain a valid phone number ? I don't want to do business with someone who advertises & lists their primary business address as a vacant lot.

title: Best maps app I’ve ever used
text: I love how convenient and handy Google Maps is to have around. Whenever I need to find information about a business or restaurant, all I need to do is enter the name or approximation into the search bar and G Maps provides me with all the details I need. The best feature I think is that it syncs my searches across devices so I can locate a place using G Maps on my iPad and then find it again quickly on my Android phone when I need to start navigating there. I also love the pinpoint precision and accuracy of Google Maps navigation. It’s like the perfect app to navigate the way to where you want to go and play around with it when you’re bored.
